Kogi State Governor Alhaji Yahaya Bello, has approved the appointment of Justice H.A.Olusiyi as acting Chief Judge of the state. The appointments followed the demise of Justices Nasiru Ajana on June 28, 2020. According to a statement issued by the Governor Chief Press Secretary, Onogwu Muhammed on Friday, the appointment is for a period of three months. Bello also approved the appointment of Justice Bayo Olowosegun as acting President of the Customary Court of Appeal, Kogi State. Justice Olowosegun replaces late Justice Shaibu Atadoga who passed on two weeks back.